The paper deals with reliable communication in a dynamic network, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and network security (cs.CR). The presence of compromised nodes and the need for resilience against them also points towards the sub-category of network and internet architecture (cs.NI). The case studies involving robots and agents suggest a possible focus on systems and control (cs.SY), while the use of algorithms for reliable communication suggests a possible focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
